action.text: Mr. Rostenkowski moved to suspend the rules and pass the resolution.
Considered under suspension of the rules.

vote.text: On motion to suspend the rules and pass the resolution Agreed to by voice vote.

Received in the Senate and read twice and referred to the Committee on Finance.
Senate Committee on Finance discharged by Unanimous Consent.

vote.text: Passed Senate without amendment by Voice Vote.

action.text: Message on Senate action sent to the House.

bill.summary: 7/13/1993--Introduced. Approves the extension of nondiscriminatory treatment (most-favored-nation treatment) to the products of Romania pursuant to the message transmitted to the Congress by the President on July 2, 1993.
